    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1004"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1004">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/8–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1004<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Economic Security Controls</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_RSJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rubin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Acting Chief of the Division of Economic
                        Security Controls</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_OCT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Oliver</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1004fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-02">August 2,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 480. For <persName corresp="#p_OCT1">Oliver</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_RSJ1">Rubin</persName>.</p>
                <p>President has sent to <persName corresp="#p_CLGLD1">General Clay</persName>
                        memo<note n="2" xml:id="d1004fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1003">Document No. 1003</ref>.</note> stating agreement of
                    Big Three to issuance of decree vesting German foreign assets, and directing
                    that <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss> (Allied Control Commission) be urged to
                    adopt decree. Memo states that President regards it as urgent that control and
                    power of disposition over German external assets be obtained. Draft of decree
                    already sent to you<note n="3" xml:id="d1004fn3">Not printed.</note> has been
                    amended by striking <pb facs="1165" n="969" xml:id="pg_969"/> portion which
                    previously set up a special board (with US and <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                    represented) to direct the vesting body.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
